Greenwood Park SAPS are investigating a case of attempted murder following a shooting incident in Durban North on Wednesday night. According to Marshall Security, reports from witnesses indicated that the victims were shot by unknown suspects, who then fled the scene in an unknown vehicle. ALSO READ | Man killed in drive-by shooting in Durban They added that the circumstances surrounding the shooting incident were not known yet. Provincial SAPS spokesperson Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo said two men sustained injuries and were rushed to hospital for medical attention. Men were sitting in a vehicle on Green Lane when they reportedly noticed a vehicle with unknown men driving towards them. The men in the other vehicle allegedly opened fire towards the victims.READ MORE High temperatures impact dam levels